# Example fragment for .env in THIS directory (next to requirements.txt).
# Ollama is not a built-in LiteLLM route with API keys; use a custom OpenAI-compatible name.
# The prefix before _API_BASE becomes the model prefix in requests: ollama_cloud/your-model
#
# Windows: the proxy venv is created at %LOCALAPPDATA%\Documind\llm-proxy-venv (short path; avoids LiteLLM MAX_PATH errors).
# 1. Set PROXY_API_KEY (and OLLAMA_CLOUD_API_BASE) in .env here once.
# 2. Documind writes real Ollama keys to documind_synced_keys.env when you Save settings (no need to duplicate keys here).
# 3. Run: start-gui.bat or scripts\start-llm-api-proxy.bat
# 4. Documind Settings:
#    - Base URL: http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1
#    - Single API Key = PROXY_API_KEY (same string as below)
#    - Multiple keys = your real Ollama Cloud keys (synced to the proxy automatically)
#    - LLM proxy model prefix: ollama_cloud

PROXY_API_KEY=change-me-to-a-long-random-secret
OLLAMA_CLOUD_API_BASE=https://ollama.com/v1
# Use ollama.com (not api.ollama.com): keys from https://ollama.com/settings/keys authenticate there;
# api.ollama.com often returns HTTP 401 for the same Bearer token.
# Bare "qwen3.5" and local-style tags (e.g. qwen3.5:9b) are rewritten to qwen3.5:cloud for Cloud.
# Do not use .../ai/v1 under api.ollama.com — that path returns marketing HTML (404).
# See https://ollama.com/library/qwen3.5:cloud — override if needed:
#OLLAMA_CLOUD_MODEL_MAP={"qwen3.5":"qwen3.5:397b-cloud"}
# Optional manual overrides (normally omit — Documind sync fills *_API_KEY_*):
# OLLAMA_CLOUD_API_KEY_1=your-ollama-cloud-key-here
